{
  "doc_id": "24525",
  "text": "With the changing ART guidelines indicating that ART should be started independently of CD4 cell count (known as the \"Test and Start\" program), an increase in the number of patients receiving ART and with higher CD4 cell counts is expected. Therefore, the pattern of OIs within PLHIV starting ART in today's resource-limited setting may change compared to our cohort. However, no increase of CD4 cell counts at ART start was observed in sub-Saharan Africa after 2009, when the CD4 threshold for ART eligibility was raised from 200 to 350 cells/ μL [CITATION_1] , and substantial proportions of patients continue to present with advanced disease in this setting [CITATION_2] .",
